SIMPLE: credible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Credible
<hw>Cred"i*ble</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ecr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>credibilis</ets>, fr. <ets>credere</ets>. See
<er>Creed</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being credited or believed;
worthy of belief; entitled to confidence; trustworthy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things are made <qex>credible</qex> either by the known condition
and quality of the utterer or by the manifest likelihood of truth in
themselves.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A very diligent and observing person, and likewise very sober and
<qex>credible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dampier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Credibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
